author: Giorgio Mendoza
description: ArmSoM has released the CM1, a compact Rockchip RK3506J-based computer-on-module for industrial control, HMI, and embedded systems. Its core-plus-carrier design offers flexibility, long lifecycle, and industrial-grade reliability, with features such as MIPI DSI display output, dual Ethernet via the carrier board, and an operating range of −40 °C to 85 °C. title: ArmSoM CM1 Core Module with RK3506J Released for Industrial and Embedded Applications

author: Giorgio Mendoza
description: Libre Computer has shared new details on its upcoming Solitude and Alta Compute Modules, designed as pin-compatible alternatives to Raspberry Pi Compute Module 4 (CM4) and Compute Module 5 (CM5) form factors. title: Libre Computer Previews Solitude and Alta Compute Modules with Low-Power Features

author: Giorgio Mendoza
description: AAEON has introduced two SMARC 2.1 compliant CPU modules powered by the MediaTek Genio platform. title: AAEON Leverages MediaTek Genio SoCs for Latest SMARC Modules uCOM-M700 and uCOM-M510
